        "created_at": "2022-03-30T14:57:08.105Z",
        "cooked": "<p>HI,<br>\nWe are running FDB on OCP/kubernetes using the operator and created the cluster.  We would like to know if there is a proper way to scale down all the pods/shutdown the cluster but keep the pvc so that we can bring them back and reuse those pvc.  I know we have to refresh the connect string when the cluster is back but just wonder is there a way to scale down/shutdown the cluster without losing those pvc.</p>",
